Third-party components
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Rime depends on third-party software, each under its own license. Dependencies are
resolved by Conan (see /conanfile.py) rather than vendored under third_party/, but are
recorded here so downstream users have a complete attribution list.

Runtime / shipped dependencies:

  - fmt — formatting library.
      Copyright (c) 2012-present, Victor Zverovich and contributors. MIT License.
  - Vulkan-Headers — Khronos Vulkan API headers (RHI Vulkan backend).
      Copyright (c) The Khronos Group Inc. Apache License 2.0.
  - volk — Vulkan meta-loader.
      Copyright (c) 2018-present, Arseny Kapoulkine. MIT License.
  - VulkanMemoryAllocator (VMA) — GPU memory allocator.
      Copyright (c) Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. (GPUOpen). MIT License.
  - libjpeg-turbo — SIMD-accelerated JPEG codec (the TurboJPEG API); the Track S wire codec.
      Copyright (c) 2009-2024 D. R. Commander and contributors; (c) 1991-2020 Thomas G. Lane,
      Guido Vollbeding (IJG). BSD-3-Clause / IJG License / zlib License.
  - lz4 — fast lossless compression; the Track S lossless streaming path.
      Copyright (c) 2011-present, Yann Collet. BSD-2-Clause License.

Build-time / tooling dependencies (not shipped in the engine binary):

  - doctest — unit-test framework (test builds only).
      Copyright (c) 2016-2023, Viktor Kirilov. MIT License.
  - glslang — GLSL-to-SPIR-V compiler, used at build time to compile shaders.
      Copyright (c) The Khronos Group Inc. and contributors. BSD-3-Clause / Apache-2.0.
  - SPIRV-Tools, SPIRV-Headers — SPIR-V tooling (transitive build dependency of glslang).
      Copyright (c) The Khronos Group Inc. Apache License 2.0 / MIT.

The Vulkan runtime loader and an ICD (a GPU driver, MoltenVK on macOS, or lavapipe in CI)
are provided by the host environment, not by Rime.
